[`FindObjectsOfType`](https://docs.unity3d.com/ScriptReference/Object.FindObjectsOfType.html) can only find components that are **enabled** and **active** in the scene hierarchy. If for any reason this is not the case in the moment you call it you won&#39;t find that component.

&gt; It will return no assets (meshes, textures, prefabs, ...) or inactive objects.

Also note

&gt; Please note that this function is very slow. [...]. In most cases you can use the singleton pattern instead.

So in your case I would rather use a singleton pattern:

    // This stays set and shared between all Level classes
    // also between scenes for the entire session
    private static Level instance;

    private void Awake()
    {
        // other instance already exists?
        if(instance)
        {
            Debug.Log(&quot;Another instance of Level already exists. Click here to highlight it in the hierarchy&quot;, instance);
            Destroy(gameObject);
            return;
        }
    
        instance = this;
        DontDestroyOnLoad(gameObject);
    }

